text: April25, 27, my friend Cheong suggest we try out this TB YTHu, I was a bit hesitate but go along. I order the soup big @ 7.90. Looking at it, quite plain. But it was good hot, Mee Hoon just nice and the chilli is ok. A good place to have lunch - a bit of good vibes. Price on the high side. We recommend to try if you are around this area for 1st timer otherwise there r much better YTF at better prices at the hawker centre.
Got the Ampang Yong Tau Hoo takeaway. It’s not bad, pretty flavourful. But felt the portion was a little too small for the price paid.
Tender tofu that when you swallow hot, it feels so wonderful and special. The place can be hot but lots of ceiling fans so it’s bearable

Average food at above-average prices.

Non-airconditioned coffeeshop.
Chee Cheong Fun with yong tau too! Tasty but also nothing super great.
